Clearly this is not evidence for evolution, but instead evidence for the only competing theory! That theory is Perverted Design. Only a Designer obsessed with sex and violence and gluttony and all those other vices would create these Irreducibly Perverse systems we see in nature, as exemplified by these marsupials. I keep trying to have my local school board acknowledge this theory and teach it to the students, but they unfairly discriminate against my viewpoint! fferitt25 wrote:FoxHound wrote:I was very confused by the end of this article. I kept waiting for the author to explain how this reproduction causes the death of male involved. Then I realized that the quoted term "suicidal reproduction" is just a misnomer for the process described at the end of the articleQuote:The huge amount of resources expended on mating, combined with the fact that survival in small mammals is pretty low to begin with, means that the males are unlikely to survive to mate a second time anyway. So instead, they simply tune their bodies to make the most out of the one chance they get. And at an average of 9.4 hours, it's hard to say that they don't accomplish this.I guess even biologists sometimes dabble in click-baiting.They also never really answered WHY.Other than theorizing that the the farther away from the euquator...blah blah blahThat issue of latitude ties in with the earlier mention of resource availability and the fact that these insectivores have adapted to time their litters to coincide with a huge (but short-lived) boom in the seasonal insect supply. The males die off and that clears the way for the offspring to eat as many insects as they can while they're available, without their fathers competing for those nutrients once the bugs start disappearing.
